    "hc_biological_scent_acegzn": {
      "type": "hc-biological-scent",
      "name": "HC Biological Scent",
      "settings": {
        "heading": "The Biological \nScent Gap",
        "body_text": "<p>For decades, the perfume and clothing industry has focused on masking odor or absorbing sweat. They conveniently forgot this fundamental truth: <strong>sweat itself is odorless.</strong></p><p>Odor is the byproduct of bacteria on your skin and in your clothes consuming the proteins and lipids in your sweat, then off-gassing (yep, bacteria farts). Said in another way, when your clothes smell that means you're constantly being crop dusted by bacteria so the issue isn't necessarily your sweat, it's what's eating your sweat.</p>",
        "card_top_label": "Sweat + Bacteria",
        "card_bottom_label": "Odor",
        "padding_top_mobile": 64,
        "padding_bottom_mobile": 64,
        "padding_top_desktop": 128,
        "padding_bottom_desktop": 128
      }
    },
