      "name": "HC Odor Types",
      "settings": {
        "heading": "The 6 Types of Odor",
        "subtext": "Most \"anti-odor\" shirts only fight one. We engineered HercLeón to neutralize all six.",
        "show_footer": true,
        "footer_left_icon": "🧬",
        "footer_left_heading": "The Genetic Lottery",
        "footer_left_body": "<p>Not everyone smells. A fascinating mutation in the ABCC11 gene—highly prevalent in East Asian populations—actually prevents the body from pumping proteins and lipids into apocrine sweat. Without those specific nutrients, the bacteria on your skin have absolutely nothing to eat, which means they produce zero body odor. Interestingly, this same gene is also responsible for determining whether you have dry or wet earwax! For the lucky few, deodorant is entirely optional. But for the rest of us, we have HercLeón.</p>",
        "footer_right_icon": "👃",
        "footer_right_heading": "Speaking in Scent",
        "footer_right_body": "<p>Before complex language, humans communicated through smell. Our body odor wasn't a faux pas; it was a highly evolved broadcast system used to signal fear, identify family, broadcast health, and even find genetically compatible mates; truthfully, no dating app can match you better than body's odor.</p><p>Ever wonder why animals like dogs and cats can tell when you're sad or sick? It's because your body is constantly broadcasting its current state. This is also why some people can instantly tell when something is \"off\" with another person; it might not be intuition, it's probably just smell.</p>",
        "padding_top_mobile": 64,
        "padding_bottom_mobile": 64,
        "padding_top_desktop": 128,
        "padding_bottom_desktop": 128
      }
    },
    "hc_stages_of_odor_mqwmx8": {
      "type": "hc-stages-of-odor",
      "blocks": {
        "stage_dLcAeH": {
          "type": "stage",
          "settings": {
            "theme": "light",
            "step_number": "01",
            "title": "Prevention",
            "body": "<p>The best way to handle odor-causing bacteria is to not have it in the first place. The most effective way of prevention is moisture management. The more you can prevent the bacteria from getting to your sweat, the better. We used one of the most powerful fibers as the core of our clothing so few other clothing prevents odor as effectively as HercLeón.</p><p>This is why plastic fibers (polyester, nylon, acrylic, etc.) are the worst because it's like wearing a plastic bag, they act like a greenhouse, trapping heat and forcing you to sweat more. It's literally the worst thing you can wear if you want to smell good. That's why within an hour of wearing polyester or nylon clothing they usually start to stink.</p><p>Now, of course, if you wear things like cotton, viscose, silk, linen and animal hair (aka wool), your clothes will be able to handle the moisture better which will help it stay cleaner longer.</p>"
          }
        },
        "stage_NEaxwx": {
          "type": "stage",
          "settings": {
            "theme": "dark",
            "step_number": "02",
            "title": "Neutralization",
            "body": "<p>Very few fibers actually perform this crucial step. While natural fibers manage moisture, they don't actively fight the bacteria that inevitably arrive. This is why neutralization is an essential part of handling and preventing odor.</p><p>This is where our proprietary matrix comes in. We embed a permanent blend of minerals and metals that actively pierce bacterial cell walls and disrupt their DNA. We don't just slow them down; we neutralize the odor-causing bacteria on contact, preventing the off-gassing process entirely. There's no clothing on earth that we're aware of that comes close to ours in this aspect. Even military grade is beneath us at this point.</p>"
          }
        },
        "stage_4fgYkj": {
          "type": "stage",
          "settings": {
            "theme": "light",
            "step_number": "03",
            "title": "Absorption & Adsorption",
            "body": "<p>Even with perfect prevention and neutralization, complex hormonal odors and environmental smells can still occur.</p><p>To combat this, we utilize highly porous materials (like volcanic ash and coconut charcoal) that act as microscopic sponges. Through both absorption and <strong>adsorption</strong>, they catch and trap any extra odor molecules that might happen naturally, locking them deep inside the fiber matrix so it helps keep your clothing smelling as good as possible. Most companies never solve for this but we also excel in this category as well.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "stage_dLcAeH",
        "stage_NEaxwx",
        "stage_4fgYkj"
      ],
